eNCA reporter, Lindokuhle Xulu has the story. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - Only a fraction of the KwaZulu-Natal flood victims will be buried this weekend. That's according to the KwaZulu-Natal Funeral Association Forum who says government is dragging its feet on the promised R15,000 for burial. READ: Home Affairs prioritises KZN flood victims The forum says because many deaths occurred in water, the bodies are decomposed and pose a medical threat if not buried soon. eNCA reporter, Lindokuhle Xulu has the story in the video above. 